Delphi Automotive PLC (NYSE:DLPH) to Release Quarterly Earnings on Wednesday

					Posted by Mitch Edgeman on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments 




Delphi Automotive PLC (NYSE:DLPH) will be announcing its earnings results before the market opens  on Wednesday, August 2nd. Analysts expect the company to announce earnings of $1.65 per share for the quarter.  Delphi Automotive PLC has set its Q2 guidance at $1.62-1.68 EPS and its FY17 guidance at $6.40-6.70 EPS.
Delphi Automotive PLC (NYSE:DLPH) last released its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, May 3rd. The auto parts company reported $1.59 earnings per share for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.46 by $0.13. Delphi Automotive PLC had a net margin of 6.90% and a return on equity of 62.09%. The company had revenue of $4.29 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $4.12 billion. During the same period last year, the firm earned $1.36 earnings per share. The firm’s revenue was up 5.9% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, analysts expect Delphi Automotive PLC to post $6.6 EPS for the current fiscal year and $7.17 EPS for the next fiscal year. 


 Get Delphi Automotive PLC alerts:



Delphi Automotive PLC (DLPH) traded down 0.24% on Thursday, hitting $90.45. 127,031 shares of the company were exchanged. The stock has a market capitalization of $24.23 billion, a P/E ratio of 21.07 and a beta of 1.38. The company has a 50 day moving average price of $88.39 and a 200-day moving average price of $81.02. Delphi Automotive PLC has a 52 week low of $60.50 and a 52 week high of $93.43. 




In related news, SVP David M. Sherbin sold 15,500 shares of Delphi Automotive PLC stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, May 17th. The stock was sold at an average price of $86.63, for a total value of $1,342,765.00. Following the completion of the sale, the senior vice president now directly owns 70,766 shares in the company, valued at $6,130,458.58. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through this hyperlink. Also, Director Sean O. Mahoney sold 1,949 shares of Delphi Automotive PLC stock in a transaction dated Friday, May 26th. The shares were sold at an average price of $87.41, for a total value of $170,362.09. Following the completion of the sale, the director now owns 11,767 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $1,028,553.47. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders sold 20,449 shares of company stock valued at $1,770,497 over the last 90 days. 0.32% of the stock is currently owned by corporate insiders. 
