NEW YORK, July 26, 2017 /PRNewswire/ --


    If you want a Stock Review on ALSN, BWA, DAN, or DLPH then come over to
http://dailystocktracker.com/register and sign up for your free customized report
today. On Tuesday, benchmark US indices were bullish as the NASDAQ Composite closed the
trading session up 0.02%; the Dow Jones Industrial Average edged 0.47% higher; and the S&P
500 was up 0.29%. Five out of nine sectors finished the day in green. Pre-market today,
DailyStockTracker.com reviews these four Auto Parts stocks: Allison Transmission Holdings
Inc. (NYSE: ALSN), BorgWarner Inc. (NYSE: BWA), Dana Inc. (NYSE: DAN), and Delphi
Automotive PLC (NYSE: DLPH). Access DailyStockTracker.com's free research reports for this
morning's stocks line-up at:


    http://dailystocktracker.com/register


    Allison Transmission 


    Indianapolis, Indiana headquartered Allison Transmission Holdings Inc.'s stock
finished Tuesday's session 0.16% lower at $37.10. A total volume of 1.60 million shares
was traded, which was higher than its three months average volume of 1.42 million shares.
 The Company's shares have advanced 25.17% in the last twelve months, and 10.12% on an YTD
basis. The stock is trading above its 200-day moving average by 5.95%. Furthermore, shares
of Allison Transmission, which together with its subsidiaries, designs, manufactures, and
sells commercial and defense fully-automatic transmissions for medium- and heavy-duty
commercial vehicles, and medium- and heavy-tactical US defense vehicles, have a Relative
Strength Index (RSI) of 41.26. Free research report on ALSN is available at:


    http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=ALSN

BorgWarner 


    Shares in Auburn Hills, Michigan headquartered BorgWarner Inc. ended at $45.84, up
2.50% from the last trading session. The stock recorded a trading volume of 1.89 million
shares. The Company's shares have gained 11.26% in the last one month, 12.24% over the
previous three months, 37.82% in the last twelve months, and 16.23% on an YTD basis. The
stock is trading above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages by 6.76% and 14.04%,
respectively. Moreover, shares of BorgWarner, which provides solutions for combustion,
hybrid, and electric vehicles worldwide, have an RSI of 62.37. The complimentary research
report on BWA can be downloaded at:


    http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=BWA

Dana 


    Maumee, Ohio headquartered Dana Inc.'s stock ended yesterday's session 0.73% higher at
$23.46. A total volume of 2.10 million shares was traded, which above than its three
months average of 1.83 million shares. The Company's shares have advanced 10.76% in the
